Kamdhenu signs Preity G Zinta as brand ambassador for its decorative paints business This collaboration will help enhance the brand''s pan-India reach and recall...                                          Dear Reader,


                                    
                                
                                
                                    

                                        Given that the return filing date has been extended many times this year, there has been plenty of time to think about personal taxes and tax savings. Although we sometimes think of tax savings as a separate target, it should really be part of your medium
                                        to long-term wealth-building strategy. That is to say when deciding whether or not to invest to save money on taxes, remember the goal of the investment.
                                    
                                

                                
                                    

                                        

                                    
                                
                                
                                    

                                        EXCLUSIVES    
                                    
                                
                                
                                    
                                        
                                            
                                        
                                    
                                

                                
                                    
                                        How to pick the right focused fund?
                                    
                                
                                
                                    

                                        Cleyon D''Souza      3 min read                                        

                                    
                                


                                
                                    
                                        You have focused funds investing in stocks of companies across different sectors and market capitalisation. It has maximum exposure to 30 stocks rather than 50-100 stocks as in diversified equity funds.

                                         Moreover, the fund manager of a focused fund allocates assets between large-cap, mid-cap, and small-cap stocks without any restrictions across different sectors to maximise your return over some time.

                                         You can invest in focused funds only if you are an aggressive investor. It helps if you have an investment horizon of over five years. You must invest in focused funds only if you are comfortable with a
                                        concentrated portfolio of limited stocks.
                                         Read more
                                    
                                

                                
                                    

                                        

                                    
                                

                                
                                    

                                        EXCLUSIVES    
                                    
                                
                                
                                    
                                        
                                            
                                        
                                    
                                

                                
                                    
                                        Submit response in the e-compliance portal for IT queries
                                    
                                
                                
                                    

                                        Namita Shah     2 min read                                        

                                    
                                


                                
                                    
                                        Many taxpayers have received notices or intimation for non-disclosure of interest on savings and fixed deposits in the income tax returns of the financial year 2020-21. It is due to the income tax department that has created an e-compliance portal that
                                        is dedicated to monitoring and evaluating specific compliance-related issues.

                                         The portal enables the income tax department to communicate the taxpayerâ€™s issue and captures response through secured electronic communication.

                                         The income tax department then verifies the online response submitted by the taxpayer. If a non-satisfactory reaction to the issue is captured, a further query may be raised, or further proceedings may
                                        be initiated. Otherwise, the matter will be closed.
                                         Read more
                                    
                                


                                
                                    

                                        

                                    
                                



                                
                                    

                                        EXCLUSIVES    
                                    
                                
                                
                                    
                                        
                                            
                                        
                                    
                                

                                
                                    
                                        Critical lessons for investors from the Archegos collapse
                                    
                                
                                
                                    

                                        Cleyon D''Souza    5 min read                                        

                                    
                                


                                
                                    
                                        Do you want to borrow and invest in the stock market? Are you looking to trade in stocks rather than invest for the long run? You may consider these critical lessons for investors from the Archegos collapse before trading in the stock market.

                                         You must understand the term â€˜leverageâ€™ before you focus on the Archegos collapse. In simple terms, leverage means using borrowed money to maximise the potential return from an investment.

                                         You could lay the blame for the Archegos crisis at the doorstep of a financial derivative instrument called a total return swap. It is a contract that permits a user to take on the profits and losses of
                                        a stock portfolio or any other asset in exchange for a fee.
                                         Read more
                                    
                                

                                
                                    

                                        

                                    
                                


                                
                                    

                                        EXCLUSIVES    
                                    
                                
                                
                                    
                                        
                                            
                                        
                                    
                                

                                
                                    
                                        Private banks might see a spike in deposits for the March quarter
                                    
                                
                                
                                    

                                        Bhavana PN     2 min read                                        

                                    
                                


                                
                                    
                                        Based on the initial numbers reported by three private banks, it has been anticipated that the Indian private lenders may record a spike in deposits for the March quarter. Retail inflation has brought down returns for savers; however, this has not stopped
                                        investors from placing their money in the form of bank deposits.

                                         Most banks emphasise gathering deposits, especially retail term deposits, current accounts, and savings accounts, to strengthen their liability franchises and bring down their dependence on bulk deposits.

                                         Bank deposits increased by 12% compared to the previous year and stood at Rs 149.55 trillion as of 12 March. HDFC Bank has reported that its deposit base has grown to about 13.35 trillion as of 31 March.
                                         Read more

Subject: Urgent :: Blue Prism Lead :: Contract  (W2 Only)/ Fulltime
Body:
CEIPAL ATS - Simplified Recruiting and Staffing

        

        
        
                        
                
                	 
                        
                            
                                
Hi 



Hope you are doing great. 



Below is the job Description , Kindly go through it and let me know your interest.



Blue Prism Lead

Contract (W2 Only)/ Fulltime 

NY/NJ (Remote Till Covid)



Job Description:

Responsibilities:


	Should have 6+yrs of experience in leading the RPA/BP implementation
	Lead the RPA development team.
	Work closely with other engineers and technical leads to complete projects on schedule and adherence to engineering processes such as code reviews, source control, and unit testing, use case analysis, and other Blue Prism SDLC and best practices.
	Collect the queries related to the requirements and get them resolved by the business person (e.g. the client, business analyst, product manager or project manager) assigned to the project.
	Create the development plan, get it reviewed and approved/ signed-off by the relevant stakeholders.
	Estimate the development effort and team (size, skills, attitude and schedule).
	Oversee various responsibilities of project until the project is delivered and deployed successfully.
	Mentor team for technical excellence.
	Resolve all the technical impediments for the project.




Demonstrated Skills and Abilities:


	Creative and Passionate Developer
	Team Player
	Life Long Learner
	Solution Delivery
	Technical Leadership
	Solution Design




Technical Skillset:


	Must have certification In Blue prism (BP  AD01), good to have BP  AP01 certification
	Must have delivered RPA solution using Blue Prism and other RPA technologies
	Hands on in development in C#.NET, VB.NET.
	Hands on Visual Studio, Versioning control tool such as Microsoft TFS, able to develop, compile, create, debug and consume .Net common components (such as DLLs).
	Hands on Database concepts such Write/modify SQL Queries(DML), Create/Modify Database Objects(DDL) , Database connection
	Good understanding of Object-oriented programming and have hands on development and unit testing experience
	Developed and maintain efficient, reusable, and reliable code
	Understanding of workflow based logic and the ability to both understand a business process from a workflow diagram and to conceptualize it as an automated solution
	Process Modeling Experience
	An aptitude for problem solving, with the ability to take a logical route to the source of an error
	A self-starter who delivers high quality work and can adapt to new challenges, either on their own or as part of a team
	Development of Exception Handling framework












Thanks in advance.



Mohammad Siddique Ansari 

Sr. Technical Recruiter

Quantum World Technologies Inc. 

199 W Hillcrest Dr, Suite#0112, Thousand Oaks, CA 91360 

http://www.quantumworld.us

Cell: 820-400-0858

Body: Hello Amaninder Hajrah,You are receiving this email because you received funding under the Ontario Ministry of Educationâ€™s Support for Learners Program (â€œSFLâ€) between November 30, 2020 and February 8, 2021.Beginning on April 26, 2021, the Ontario government will provide another round of direct payments to families and students through a new program, the Ontario Covid-19 Child Benefit (OCCB), which provides financial support to families with young learners and students to help with additional educational costs they have incurred during the COVID-19 pandemic. Your new Ontario Covid-19 Child Benefit (OCCB) confirmation number is:444225217 for An***. Payment will be made by Interac E-Transfer, which was the payment method that you selected in your Support for Learners (SFL) application. You will not be able to change the method of payment selected for the Ontario COVID-19 Child Benefit.Under the OCCB program, you will automatically receive a one-time payment of:â€¢	$400 for each child or youth up to Grade 12â€¢	$500 for each child or youth up to age 21 with special needsAutomatic Payment You will automatically receive the new Ontario Covid-19 Child Benefit (OCCB) payments. You do not need to submit a new online application for the Ontario Covid-19 Child Benefit. The Ministry of Education will use the information provided in your Support for Learners application to issue this new benefit. Please note that this new Ontario Covid-19 Child Benefit is a one-time payment only. Attempts to submit a duplicate application for the same child will not result in another payment. Payment MethodsPayment by InteracIf you received your SFL payment(s) via Interac e-transfer, you will also receive your OCCB payment(s) via Interac e-transfer. Tip: To easily receive this payment, turn on the â€œauto-depositâ€ feature on your online banking. With the â€œauto-depositâ€ feature turned on, you wonâ€™t have to answer a security question to deposit your payment(s). For help turning on the â€œauto-depositâ€™ feature, please contact your bank. You will receive another email shortly with instructions on how to deposit your Interac e-transfer. Payment by Direct Deposit If you were sent your SFL payment(s) via Direct Deposit, you will receive your OCCB payment(s) via Direct Deposit to the same bank account provided in your SFL application. Please check your bank account or call your bank to confirm a payment from Support for Learners. Please do not call our helpline until after you have called your bank to confirm.Payment by ChequeIf you were sent your SFL payment(s) via Cheque, you will receive your OCCB payment(s) via Cheque â€“ please note it may take up to several weeks to receive your automatic payment by cheque. Expected Payment DateOntario Covid-19 Child Benefit payments should be issued by May 14, 2021. If you have more than one child, you may not receive all your payments at the same time. If you do not receive your payment(s) by May 10, 2021 or if you require assistance please contact the OCCB Helpline at 1-888-444-3770 and Toll-free TTY: 1-800-268-7095. Terms and Conditions1.	Purpose of Program The purpose of the Ontario Covid-19 Child Benefit (OCCB) program is to provide financial support to families with young learners to help with additional educational costs they have incurred during the COVID-19 pandemic. 2.	EligibilityEligibility to receive an automatic payment under the OCCB program is based on your eligibility for the Support for Learners program.  By receiving the OCCB payment, you confirm that the eligibility information provided in your Support for Learners application was accurate and true. Payments will be delayed or denied if the information you provided was incomplete or inaccurate. 3.	Corroborating documentation may be requestedFrom time to time, the Ministry of Education may contact you to request corroborating documentation to confirm your eligibility. The Ministry of Education reserves the right to deny payments in the absence of such corroborating documentation.4.	Support payment fraudIf an OCCB payment is paid out to you and it is determined that you were ineligible for the payment, you will be required to repay that money promptly. The Ministry of Education reserves the right to take any other corrective action it deems necessary in such circumstances, including initiating a civil action to reclaim funds and referring suspected fraudulent claims to the police for investigation.  5.	ForumThe laws of the Province of Ontario apply.By receiving an OCCB payment, you agree to the above-noted terms and conditions of this funding.  Please see Ontario.ca/page/get-ontario-covid-19-child-benefit for more information.  pour les enfants en raison de la COVID-19
Body: Hello Amaninder Hajrah,You are receiving this email because you received funding under the Ontario Ministry of Educationâ€™s Support for Learners Program (â€œSFLâ€) between November 30, 2020 and February 8, 2021.Beginning on April 26, 2021, the Ontario government will provide another round of direct payments to families and students through a new program, the Ontario Covid-19 Child Benefit (OCCB), which provides financial support to families with young learners and students to help with additional educational costs they have incurred during the COVID-19 pandemic. Your new Ontario Covid-19 Child Benefit (OCCB) confirmation number is:444225217 for An***. Payment will be made by Interac E-Transfer, which was the payment method that you selected in your Support for Learners (SFL) application. You will not be able to change the method of payment selected for the Ontario COVID-19 Child Benefit.Under the OCCB program, you will automatically receive a one-time payment of:â€¢	$400 for each child or youth up to Grade 12â€¢	$500 for each child or youth up to age 21 with special needsAutomatic Payment You will automatically receive the new Ontario Covid-19 Child Benefit (OCCB) payments. You do not need to submit a new online application for the Ontario Covid-19 Child Benefit. The Ministry of Education will use the information provided in your Support for Learners application to issue this new benefit. Please note that this new Ontario Covid-19 Child Benefit is a one-time payment only. Attempts to submit a duplicate application for the same child will not result in another payment. Payment MethodsPayment by InteracIf you received your SFL payment(s) via Interac e-transfer, you will also receive your OCCB payment(s) via Interac e-transfer. Tip: To easily receive this payment, turn on the â€œauto-depositâ€ feature on your online banking. With the â€œauto-depositâ€ feature turned on, you wonâ€™t have to answer a security question to deposit your payment(s). For help turning on the â€œauto-depositâ€™ feature, please contact your bank. You will receive another email shortly with instructions on how to deposit your Interac e-transfer. Payment by Direct Deposit If you were sent your SFL payment(s) via Direct Deposit, you will receive your OCCB payment(s) via Direct Deposit to the same bank account provided in your SFL application. Please check your bank account or call your bank to confirm a payment from Support for Learners. Please do not call our helpline until after you have called your bank to confirm.Payment by ChequeIf you were sent your SFL payment(s) via Cheque, you will receive your OCCB payment(s) via Cheque â€“ please note it may take up to several weeks to receive your automatic payment by cheque. Expected Payment DateOntario Covid-19 Child Benefit payments should be issued by May 14, 2021. If you have more than one child, you may not receive all your payments at the same time. If you do not receive your payment(s) by May 10, 2021 or if you require assistance please contact the OCCB Helpline at 1-888-444-3770 and Toll-free TTY: 1-800-268-7095. Terms and Conditions1.	Purpose of Program The purpose of the Ontario Covid-19 Child Benefit (OCCB) program is to provide financial support to families with young learners to help with additional educational costs they have incurred during the COVID-19 pandemic. 2.	EligibilityEligibility to receive an automatic payment under the OCCB program is based on your eligibility for the Support for Learners program.  By receiving the OCCB payment, you confirm that the eligibility information provided in your Support for Learners application was accurate and true. Payments will be delayed or denied if the information you provided was incomplete or inaccurate. 3.	Corroborating documentation may be requestedFrom time to time, the Ministry of Education may contact you to request corroborating documentation to confirm your eligibility. The Ministry of Education reserves the right to deny payments in the absence of such corroborating documentation.4.	Support payment fraudIf an OCCB payment is paid out to you and it is determined that you were ineligible for the payment, you will be required to repay that money promptly. The Ministry of Education reserves the right to take any other corrective action it deems necessary in such circumstances, including initiating a civil action to reclaim funds and referring suspected fraudulent claims to the police for investigation.  5.	ForumThe laws of the Province of Ontario apply.By receiving an OCCB payment, you agree to the above-noted terms and conditions of this funding.  Please see Ontario.ca/page/get-ontario-covid-19-child-benefit for more information. If you have any questions about this, please contact us at 1-888-444-3770 and Toll-free TTY: 1-800-268-7095.Thank you,Ontario COVID-19 Child Benefit Team Bonjour Amaninder Hajrah,Vous recevez ce courriel parce que vous avez reÃ§u du financement en vertu du Programme de soutien aux apprenants (SA) du ministÃ¨re de lâ€™Ã‰ducation de lâ€™Ontario entre le 30 novembre 2020 et le 8 fÃ©vrier 2021.Ã€ partir du 26 avril 2021, le gouvernement de lâ€™Ontario offrira une autre sÃ©rie de paiements directs aux familles et aux Ã©lÃ¨ves par lâ€™entremise dâ€™un nouveau programme, la Prestation ontarienne pour les enfants en raison de la COVID-19 (POEC), qui fournit une aide financiÃ¨re aux familles avec de jeunes Ã©lÃ¨ves et apprenants pour aider Ã  couvrir les frais dâ€™Ã©ducation supplÃ©mentaires engagÃ©s pendant la pandÃ©mie de COVID-19. Subject: Urgent :: Blue Prism Lead :: Contract  (W2 Only)/ Fulltime
Body:
CEIPAL ATS - Simplified Recruiting and Staffing

        

        
        
                        
                
                	 
                        
                            
                                
Hi 



Hope you are doing great. 



Below is the job Description , Kindly go through it and let me know your interest.



Blue Prism Lead

Contract (W2 Only)/ Fulltime 

NY/NJ (Remote Till Covid)



Job Description:

Responsibilities:


	Should have 6+yrs of experience in leading the RPA/BP implementation
	Lead the RPA development team.
	Work closely with other engineers and technical leads to complete projects on schedule and adherence to engineering processes such as code reviews, source control, and unit testing, use case analysis, and other Blue Prism SDLC and best practices.
	Collect the queries related to the requirements and get them resolved by the business person (e.g. the client, business analyst, product manager or project manager) assigned to the project.
	Create the development plan, get it reviewed and approved/ signed-off by the relevant stakeholders.
	Estimate the development effort and team (size, skills, attitude and schedule).
	Oversee various responsibilities of project until the project is delivered and deployed successfully.
	Mentor team for technical excellence.
	Resolve all the technical impediments for the project.




Demonstrated Skills and Abilities:


	Creative and Passionate Developer
	Team Player
	Life Long Learner
	Solution Delivery
	Technical Leadership
	Solution Design




Technical Skillset:


	Must have certification In Blue prism (BP  AD01), good to have BP  AP01 certification
	Must have delivered RPA solution using Blue Prism and other RPA technologies
	Hands on in development in C#.NET, VB.NET.
	Hands on Visual Studio, Versioning control tool such as Microsoft TFS, able to develop, compile, create, debug and consume .Net common components (such as DLLs).
	Hands on Database concepts such Write/modify SQL Queries(DML), Create/Modify Database Objects(DDL) , Database connection
	Good understanding of Object-oriented programming and have hands on development and unit testing experience
	Developed and maintain efficient, reusable, and reliable code
	Understanding of workflow based logic and the ability to both understand a business process from a workflow diagram and to conceptualize it as an automated solution
	Process Modeling Experience
	An aptitude for problem solving, with the ability to take a logical route to the source of an error
	A self-starter who delivers high quality work and can adapt to new challenges, either on their own or as part of a team
	Development of Exception Handling framework












Thanks in advance.



Mohammad Siddique Ansari 

Sr. Technical Recruiter

Quantum World Technologies Inc. 

199 W Hillcrest Dr, Suite#0112, Thousand Oaks, CA 91360 

http://www.quantumworld.us

Cell: 820-400-0858

            An Insta moment for pre-teens
            Prasad Sangameshwaran-->
            
            

            An Insta moment for pre-teens
            
            -->
            
            
            

            Dear Readers
            Children are never too small to take classes over zoom. Then why should they be too small for Instagram?

In the post Covid-19 scenario, we have even heard of preschoolers being coached in zoom classrooms. But certain child advocacy groups believe that children in their pre-teens are not yet ready for a junior version of Instagram.


Yesterday, news broke that advocates for children from around the world had urged Facebook chief Mark Zuckerberg to ditch plans for a version of Instagram geared toward pre-teens.

Groups like The Campaign for a Commercial-free Childhood and the Electronic Privacy Information Center are among nearly 100 groups and individuals from North America, Europe, Africa and Australia to make the plea in a letter to Zuckerberg.

Instagram exploits young people''s fear of missing out and desire for peer approval, the letter contended.


But one could argue that the two prime points of their contention; fear of missing out (FOMO) or the desire for peer approval is going to be around, whether a junior version of Instagram targets pre-teens or not.


Take this example. Post the lockdown last year, many urban families made a dash for tourist locales or the lush green unexplored countryside, even as restrictions were barely lifted. The publicity of such voyeurism, either through Facebook posts, or WhatsApp status updates, was not lost on pre-teens who in turn questioned their families, why arent we out there? There was no commercial intent here. Folks were just showing-off. But peer pressure and the FOMO factor were in abundance.


In the absence of an Insta for pre-teens, theres no guarantee that a pre-teen is not already familiar with the social medium. Remember, they are often steps ahead of the older generation. After all, when parents and grandparents made a run to open their Facebook accounts, teens and young adults deserted the medium in droves, or opened accounts in fictitious names to throw their prying parents off the trail. Child advocacy groups should know better than that.

Francis Becker

Description: 2 of the 3 prints came out spectacular. I was so happy with Bestcanvas and my decision to choose Bestcanvas. But, when I opened the third print, there were 2 issues with it.: 1) 2 corners of the canvas are damaged. Not sure if it happened in transit or while stretching the canvas on the frame. 2) The photo came out very dark compared to the one I had printed from another provider (including that as a refernce as well). May be the other provider does correction of the photos before printing and bestcanvas does not. In both cases the photo is usable. Now the best solution I have is reprinting a corrected version of the photo I can provide. In order to minimize your cost, I want to get it printed in a smaller size that the original order as well. Please refer to the attached images and let me know if you can help me here. I am going to be a repeat customer and would appreciate your help in this case.
